Title: The standard model in noncommutative geometry and fermion doubling
Authors: J. M. Gracia-Bondia, B.Iochum, T. Schucker (Marseille)
Comments: 9 pages LaTeX
Report-no: CPT--97/P.3503, DFTUZ/97/08, UCR--FM--11--97
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B416 (1998) 123-128
\\
  The link between chirality in the fermion sector and (anti-)self-duality in
the boson sector is reexamined in the light of Connes' noncommutative geometry
approach to the Standard Model. We find it to impose that the noncommutative
Yang-Mills action be symmetrized in an analogous way to the Dirac-Yukawa
operator itself.
